    <!-- Help -->

    <string name="help_mortgage_type_info"><b><i>Constant loan payments</i></b>
        \nMost popular amortization schedule (fixed rate mortgage). Monthly payment (interest plus principal) is constant over the loan term. Interest rate is fixed.
        \n\n<b><i>Constant principal payments</i></b>
        \nThe principal paid, not the total monthly payment, remains constant, while total monthly payments decrease due to decreasing monthly interest. 
        Interest rate is fixed. Amortization schedule popular in Europe.</string>

    <string name="help_general"><b>Amortization type</b>
        \n<i>Constant loan payments</i>
        \nMost popular amortization schedule (fixed rate mortgage). Monthly payment (interest plus principal) is constant over the loan term. Interest rate is fixed.
        \n<i>Constant principal payments</i>
        \nThe principal paid, not the total monthly payment, remains constant, while total monthly payments decrease due to decreasing monthly interest. Interest rate is fixed. Amortization schedule popular in Europe.
        \n\n<b>Purchase price</b>\nPurchased property price.
        \n\n<b>Down payment</b>\nAmount paid in cash at the onset of the loan.
        \n\n<b>Loan amount</b>\nValue of the loan (purchase price - downpayment)
        \n\n<b>Interest rate</b>\nAnnual interest rate (nominal).
        \n\n<b>Mortgage term</b>\nThe length of time the mortgage terms and conditions (including interest rate) are in effect.
        \n\n<b>Home insurance</b>\nAnnual insurance against risks to the property.
        \n\n<b>Property tax</b>\nAnnual property (or millage) tax.
        \n\n<b>Closing fees</b>\nThe total of one-time fees (attorney, survey, application fees, etc.).
        \n\n<b>PMI</b>\nPrivate Mortgage Insurance, paid to the lender if the down payment is lower than 20\u0025 of the purchased property price or when the loan-to-value ratio is lower than 80\u0025. Loan-to-value ratio is a ratio of the loan to the value of an asset purchased.
        \n\n<b>Extra payment</b>\nMonthly or yearly additional payment that reduces the costs and term of the loan.
        \n\n<b># of payments</b>\nThe total number of payments to pay off the loan amount.
        \n\nCompounding is monthly.
        \nMax number of mortgages stored is 20.
        \nMax number of mortgages to compare is 6.
        
        </string>
        
